Charlotte Nikoi disappeared while hiking with her husband and 16-year-old daughter on Human Rights Day. CAPE TOWN - There is still no trace of a 50-year-old Ghanaian woman who went missing on Table Mountain last month. Charlotte Nikoi disappeared while hiking with her husband and 16-year-old daughter on Human Rights Day. Her husband believes she has been kidnapped. Chris Nikoi says he and his wife were in Cape Town to celebrate their 22nd wedding anniversary. He lives and works in Johannesburg, while she is based in New York as a Unicef associate director. Nikoi believes his wife has been abducted. She is somewhere in South Africa, as to whereabouts that I don t know. Their 16-year-old daughter was hiking with them on the day of Charlotte Nikoi's disappearance.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)